*''Tehillim - Three Movements'' par le {{lien|Schönberg Ensemble|lang=nl}} dirigé par {{lien|Reinbert de Leeuw|lang=nl}} et le [[London Symphony Orchestra|London Symphony Orchestra]] dirigé par [[Michael Tilson Thomas|Michael Tilson Thomas]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 1994
*''Tehillim'', par l'ensemble [[Steve Reich and Musicians|Steve Reich and Musicians]], [[ECM Records|ECM Records]], 1994.
*''The Cave'', par le [[Steve Reich Ensemble|Steve Reich Ensemble]] dirigé par [[Paul Hillier|Paul Hillier]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 1995
*''Proverb - Nagoya Marimbas - City Life'', par le [[Theater of Voices|Theater of Voices]] et le [[Steve Reich Ensemble|Steve Reich Ensemble]] dirigés par [[Paul Hillier|Paul Hillier]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 1996.
*''Music for 18 Musicians'', par l'ensemble [[Steve Reich and Musicians|Steve Reich and Musicians]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 1997.
*''[[Reich Remixed|Reich Remixed]]'', collectif, [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 1999
*''Triple Quartet - Electric Guitar phase - Music for a Large Ensemble - Tokyo/Vermont Counterpoint'', par le [[Kronos Quartet|Kronos Quartet]] et le [[Steve Reich Ensemble|Steve Reich Ensemble]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 2001.
*''Three Tales'', par l'ensemble [[Steve Reich and Musicians|Steve Reich and Musicians]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 2003.
*''You Are (Variations) - Cello Counterpoint'', par la Los Angeles Master Choral et Maya Beiser, [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 2005.
*Coffrets ''Steve Reich - Phases'' (10 disques) et ''Steve Reich - Works 1965-1995'' (5 disques), [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 2006.
*''Sextet, Piano Phase, Eight Lines'' par le [[Steve Reich and Musicians|London Steve Reich Ensemble]], CPO, 2007.
*''Daniel Variations - Variations for Vibes, Pianos & Strings'', par la Los Angeles Master Choral et le [[London Sinfonietta|London Sinfonietta]], [[Nonesuch Records|Nonesuch Records]], 2008.

== Bibliografie ==

*  Steve Reich  , Writings About Music , The Press of the Nova Scotia College of Art and Design (1974).
* Steve Reich  , Écrits et entretiens sur la musique , Paris  , Bourgois (1981).
*  Jacques-Emmanuel Fousnaquer, Claude Gayman, Christian Leble, ''Musiciens de notre temps'', Rennes, Éditions Plume, 1992, 542 pages.
*  Keith Potter, Four Musical Minimalists: La Monte Young, Terry Riley, Steve Reich, Philip Glass, [[Cambridge University Press|Cambridge University Press]] (2000).
*  D.J. Hoek, ''Steve Reich: A Bio-Bibliography'', Greenwood Press, 2001
*  Writings on Music 1965-2000 , Steve Reich , [[Oxford University Press|Oxford University Press]]  , 2002.
*  Robert Fink , Repeating Ourselves: American Minimal Music as Cultural Practice , [[University of California Press|University of California Press]] , 2005.
*  Jérôme Bodon-Clair  , Le Langage de Steve Reich, l'exemple de « Music for 18 Musicians (1976) » , Paris  , [[L'Harmattan|L'Harmattan]] , 2008








